@node "support" "Want to support me and my work?"
@{b}Want to support me and my work?@{ub}

  As you already have noticed, TUP is Freeware now. If you like
  TUP and/or other programs by me and you want to show me a little
  bit support of yours for my work, why not register an other program
  of mine?

  For example, why not register my NewInstaller? (which is also used
  in TUP for the installation). The registration of NewInstaller is
  really cheap. It costs only 10 DM ($8 US-Dollar) via E-Mail. If you
  want to show me some support, this would certainly be a nice way
  to do it.

  You can download the NewInstaller demo-version from Aminet
  (util/wb/NewInstaller1_5.lha) or my homepage (http://airsoft.home.pages.de/).

  Thanks for your support.

@endnode
   
@node "freeware" "TUP is Freeware now"
@{b}TUP is Freeware now@{ub}

  From version 1.2 on, TUP is no more Shareware. This version is fully
  functional and Freeware, that means everyone may copy and use it, as
  long as no modifications are made and it has not be sold for more
  than 5 DM or 3$ US.

  The reason why I`ve released TUP as Freeware is, that I didn`t manage
  it to get the supervise mode working correctly. Of course I got it to
  work, but it was very unstable and that is very bad for a program which
  shall run silently in the background.

  I`m still working to get that supervise feature working bugfree and if
  it does, I`ll immediately release a new version which will be Freeware
  either. Even if I get it working, TUP will never be Shareware again.

  If the registered users think now, they have paid for nothing...No that`s
  absolutely not correct. You showed your support and encouraged me to
  continue my Amiga work which is really big, as you might know. (Have a
  look on my homepage to find out how many I did for Amiga). And please
  don`t think that releasing TUP as Freeware would mean to stop the
  development....that`s WRONG!!

  Thanks to the registered users (although that are only very few!)

  Now enjoy this version and send me feedback,

  Andreas

  E-Mail: Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de
  WWW: http://www.home.pages.de/~Airsoft

@endnode

@node "hints" "Files to check/supervise"
@{b}Files to check/supervise@{ub}

  You should let TUP check this files:

  - C:Setpatch
  - C:Assign
  - C:IPrefs
  - C:Execute
  - <any program you`re using daily>

  If you select more than 20 files to check I think you`ll
  notice if TUP checks them. Otherwise you won`t notice it.
  You`ll hear your harddisk sounds then every x minutes 
  for 2 or 3 secs.
 
  Supervise support has been removed because it was too buggy,
  sorry!

  (You should let TUP supervise this files:

  - Sys:System/Format
  - C:Format
  - C:NewCLI
  - <any program that can do damage to your harddisk>

  Click in the prefs editor on "Set Standard" and those files
  will be automatically added to your list.)

@endnode

@node "wasmacht" "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}

  The Ultimate Protector, from now on called TUP, is a virus
  protector for your Amiga System. TUP is NOT a viruskiller
  it`s a system protector - it gives you information when
  viruses are in memory!

  TUP runs in the background and if it finds anything
  strange, you`ll be warned. So the virus cannot infect
  your whole system. The virus infects one file and then
  TUP pops up and you know that there is a virus and you
  can kill it with your favourite viruskiller!

  Here are some features of The Ultimate Protector:

  - detects all viruses which change files (and I think all are
    changing files, aren`t they?)
  - runs in background as a commodity
  - nice GUI
  - easy to use
  - Online help

  The main advantage of TUP is that it`ll recognize viruses which
  will be written in the future. A viruskiller can only find existing
  viruses! The most viruses start infecting some files which are
  present on every Amiga system like Assign, Execute, Mount etc. 
  With TUP you can let these files checked every x minutes and so
  you`ll be warned if a file has been changed.

  TUP gives you the security you need for your system! Install it
  now and don`t let any f*cking virus kill your system!

  It`s even Freeware now!

@endnode

