@node "System" "System requirements"
@{b}System requirements@{ub}

  Hardware requirements:
  ----------------------

  - Amiga with at least OS2.04
  - Harddisk with ~200kb free space and installed Workbench


  Software requirements:
  ----------------------

  - NewInstaller tool (util/wb/NewInstaller1_5.lha)
  - Commodore`s Installer tool located in C: (it`s on your Workbench disks)
  - reqtools.library V38+ by Niço François
  - a Viruskiller for killing the viruses detected by TUP

@endnode

@node "ques" "TUP usage"
@{b}TUP usage@{ub}

  Note! You can launch the GUI a) via exchange: Start
				  Tools/Commodities/Exchange
 				  and click on Display
				  Interface at The Ultimate
				  Protector

			       b) via tooltypes: Change
				  the tooltypes to CX_POPUP=YES

  TUP knows four different tooltypes:

  1) CX_POPUP -> If this tooltype is set, TUP will popup at
     start. If it`s in brackets or not there TUP will hide and
     you can launch it either through Exchange or the WB`s Tools
     menu. Of course if you`ve set a hotkey it`ll popup if you
     press it.

  2) CX_POPKEY = hotkey -> If you supply a hotkey definition to 
     this tooltype TUP will popup or close down when this combination
     is pressed. If TUP is iconified when you press the hotkey it`ll
     popup. If TUP is opened and you press the hotkey it`ll iconify.

  3) PREFSDIR = Path -> If you specify a pathname here, TUP will read and
     save the prefs files from and to that path. If you do not specify
     anything here, TUP will save the prefs files to S:. You can also
     specify PROGDIR: as the path.

  4) DONOTADD -> If you set this tooltype, TUP won't add itself to the
     Workbench's tools menu. This tooltype is not really necessary, but
     was strongly requested by an user, so it's here now.

  You should reboot your system after installation and if TUP is stored in
  WBStartup it runs silently in background and you won`t mind that it`s
  working :)
 
  You can work now as usual with your Amiga! If TUP detects that a file
  has been changed it displays the following:

  A file was changed: If that message appears a file TUP checks
  was changed! If you haven`t changed this file - ALERT! Take
  a viruskiller now and check the file. There are several buttons
  you can select too: 

  Delete:    Kills the possibly infected file from your harddisk.

  Write log: Writes the filename in TUP`s log file. You can
             later when the viruskiller was started have a look
             in this file and you needn`t check all files. The
             logfile of TUP is stored in S: and named TUP.log.
             You can open it with your favourite texteditor and
             see which files are logged in it.

  Nothing:   Continues procedure. This option is recommended if
             you`ve changed the file.

  Help:      Online help for the buttons.     

  If you`ve made a decision another requester appears asking you
  whether you want the prefsfile to be updated or not. If you do not
  let the prefsfile updated, you`ll get the requester of 'Warning!
  The file blabla has changed...' every time TUP checks the files.
  You should only choose 'Update Prefs' if you`re absolutely sure
  that no virus is in the file. 

  You can get hints how to configure TUP @{"here" link "hints"}. 
  There`s also information which files you should let TUP check!

  If you want to use TUP regurarly now, you can copy it to your
  WBStartup drawer and it`ll run in the background silently.

@endnode

@node "history" "Program`s History"
@{b}History@{ub}

  V1.8: (Freeware Release Version)

  · updated AmigaGuide® documentation
  · new Spanish catalog by Damaso Dominguez
  · updated German catalog, catalog description and translation
  · added DONOTADD tooltype which forces TUP to not add itself to the
    Workbench's tools menu (requested by Burkhard Breuer)

  V1.7: (Freeware Release Version)

  · updated AmigaGuide® documentation
  · updated German catalog
  · added updated Spanish catalog by Damaso Dominguez
  · updated catalog description and translation 
  · code optimizations
  · added version string to the TUP executable 
  · added 'Use Prefs' button and fixed problems with the 'Cancel' button
    (reported by Burkhard Breuer)
  · added button that opens a file requester to the 'Files to check' window
    (suggested by Burkhard Breuer)
  · fixed several problems that occurred when one tried to press buttons
    in a lower window; all windows apart from the highest are locked now
    (reported by Burkhard Breuer)

  V1.6: (Freeware Release Version)

  · updated and enhanced the AmigaGuide® documentation
  · updated installation
  · updated German catalog
  · updated catalog description and translation
  · changed the reqtools code again; damn bugs :-) It should REALLY work now!
    (otherwise I`m going crazy)
  · Preferences window will be closed now when saving the prefs (suggested by
    Burkhard Breuer)
  · fixed a bug that you couldn`t use a sub-directory when using PROGDIR:
    (reported by Burkhard Breuer) 
  · optimized the code
  · TUP acts now more like a real commodity. If you start it again while it is
    iconified, it`ll open the GUI (suggested by Burkhard Breuer)
  · fully recoded the reqtools.library access. No more Enforcer hits here, I hope
    (reported by Burkhard Breuer)
  · added 'Cancel'-button to the preferences. Effect is the same than pressing the
    close gadget (suggested by Burkhard Breuer)
  · redesigned logo in the GUI [old one was outdated...TUP9x, it is now TUP2k :)]
  · fixed some bugs concerning font sensitivety. Sorry, I was really blind :-)
  · TUP reacts now to the Escape key. Whenever you press that key, TUP
    will close its front window. When you press the Escape key in the
    main window, TUP will iconify (suggested by Burkhard Breuer)

  V1.5: (Freeware Release Version)

  · updated AmigaGuide® documentation
  · fixed some other bugs that might occur with Visual Prefs (it made TUP
    very unstable)
  · fixed the bug that there was no text in the buttons with VisualPrefs
    (reported by Ulrich Falke)
  · added French catalog by Didier Giron 
  · added updated Spanish catalog by Damaso Dominguez

  V1.4: (Freeware Release Version)

  · updated AmigaGuide® documentation
  · fixed some bugs
  · fixed some problems with VisualPrefs
  · added spanish catalog Damaso Dominguez
  · added italian catalog by Nicola Stufano

  V1.3: (Freeware Release Version)

  · added swedish catalog by Fredrik Ismyren
  · updated AmigaGuide® documentation
  · updated german catalogs and developer files
  · nearly all the suggestions/bugs in this release were reported by Burkhard
    Breuer. Thank you!
  · TUP can only be started once now
  · redesigned the logo of TUP in the GUI
  · some other minor changes
  · prefs files are now re-read after they have been changed
  · TUP now also recognizes files which have been deleted from harddisk
  · fixed a bug that occured sometimes and made TUP use wrong filenames
    (C:IPre* etc...)
  · added new tooltype PREFSDIR which allows you to set the dir where the
    prefs files (TUP.distance, TUPCheck.prefs & TUP.log) will be saved to
  · close gadget iconifies TUP now instead of quitting it
  · added button 'Quit' to the main window
  · added button 'Save Prefs' to the prefs window
  · default number for check minutes should be 1 now (I hope...)
  · fixed a bug that happened when pressing 'Cancel' in the requester that
    asks for the minutes to check

  V1.2: (Freeware Release Version)

  · updated AmigaGuide® documentation
  · major code cleanup and optimization
  · replaced installscript by a NewInstaller icon
  · added german catalogs and ct+cd files
  · added locale.library support
  · added new tooltype CX_POPKEY which allows you to assign a popkey to TUP
  · TUP adds itself now to the WB Tools menu while it`s running
  · removed supervise support: too buggy
  · removed keyfile code
  · some bugfixes

  V1.1: (Internal Beta Version)

  · added fontsensitive GUI

  V1.0: (Shareware Release Version)

  · added GUI
  · added more functions
  · added supervise support
  · runs as a commodity
  · Amiga Guide® Documentation

  V0.9: (Internal Beta Version)

  · for my private use only


  Future plans:

  - Check of OS Functions
  - more options
  - your suggestion -> contact @{"me" link "autor"}

@endnode

@node "pe" "The TUP Prefs"
@{b}The TUP preferences@{ub}

  With the help of TUP`s Prefs Editor you can easily
  configure TUP.

  Click on...

  Set files to check: You can define the files to check here. Click
                      on the 'Add' button to add a file to the
                      list or on the 'Remove' button to remove a
                      file from the list. If you click the close
                      gadget of the window the list will be saved
                      and activated.

  Set minutes: TUP checks all x minutes all the files -
               here you can set the minutes

  Save Prefs: If you click on this button TUP will save the
              preferences and initialize them.

  Cancel: If you click this button, the preferences window will
          close without saving anything.

@endnode  

 
